hands_on_practices.problem:
In a large–aspect-ratio, axisymmetric tokamak, consider linear, ideal magnetohydrodynamic shear Alfvén dynamics with equilibrium magnetic field $\mathbf{B}$, mass density $\rho$, Alfvén speed $v_{A} = |\mathbf{B}| / \sqrt{\mu_{0} \rho}$, and safety factor $q(r)$. In cylindrical geometry, the shear Alfvén continuum satisfies $\omega^{2} = k_{\parallel}^{2}(r) v_{A}^{2}$. In a torus with toroidal mode number $n$ and poloidal mode number $m$, use $k_{\parallel}(r) R_{0} \approx n - m/q(r)$ for the local parallel wavenumber, where $R_{0}$ is the major radius. Toroidicity introduces coupling between adjacent poloidal harmonics $m$ and $m+1$.

Assume a local two–component Fourier–amplitude representation for a gap mode near the avoided crossing of the two continuum branches $\omega_{m}(r) = |k_{\parallel}(m;r)| v_{A}$ and $\omega_{m+1}(r) = |k_{\parallel}(m+1;r)| v_{A}$. In the large–aspect–ratio limit, neglect kinetic effects and compressibility, and model the toroidicity-induced coupling by a real, symmetric, positive coefficient $V$ to obtain a $2 \times 2$ Hermitian eigenproblem for the poloidal amplitudes $a_{m}$ and $a_{m+1}$:
$$
\begin{pmatrix}
\omega^{2} - \omega_{m}^{2}(r)  V \\
V  \omega^{2} - \omega_{m+1}^{2}(r)
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
a_{m} \\ a_{m+1}
\end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix}
0 \\ 0
\end{pmatrix}.
$$
Define the gap center $r = r_{c}$ by the condition $\omega_{m}^{2}(r_{c}) = \omega_{m+1}^{2}(r_{c}) \equiv \omega_{c}^{2}$. The two eigenmodes at $r_{c}$ correspond to the upper and lower gap branches that arise from the avoided crossing. Using only the fundamental relations stated above, derive the eigenvectors at the gap center and compute the ordered pair of relative contributions of the adjacent poloidal components,
$$\left( \frac{a_{m+1}}{a_{m}} \right)_{\text{upper}}, \quad \left( \frac{a_{m+1}}{a_{m}} \right)_{\text{lower}},$$
for the upper–branch and lower–branch gap modes, respectively. Then explain how parity constraints for Toroidal Alfvén Eigenmodes (TAE) and Reversed Shear Alfvén Eigenmodes (RSAE) emerge from the coupling structure and the symmetry of the $2 \times 2$ system at the gap center.

Provide your final answer as the ordered pair $\left( \left( a_{m+1}/a_{m} \right)_{\text{upper}}, \left( a_{m+1}/a_{m} \right)_{\text{lower}} \right)$ in exact form, without units and without rounding.
